.TH "device_for_each_child" 9 "device_for_each_child" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
device_for_each_child \- device child iterator.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" device_for_each_child
.BI "(struct device *parent "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "int (*fn)(struct device *dev, void *data) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "parent" 12
parent struct device.
.IP "data" 12
data for the callback.
.IP "fn" 12
function to be called for each device.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Iterate over \fIparent\fP's child devices, and call \fIfn\fP for each,
passing it \fIdata\fP.

We check the return of \fIfn\fP each time. If it returns anything
other than 0, we break out and return that value.
